data.meta_description:
3 likes, 0 comments - fbc_news_fiji on June 25, 2024: "Fiji Labour Party Leader, Mahendra Chaudhry says the 2024/25 national budget must address the larger socio-economic problems in Fiji, the most urgent being poverty and the high cost of living.

Chaudhry suggests VAT rate must be reduced to nine percent.

He adds the increase in VAT was a blunder with grave consequences on poverty and the quality of life of the Fijian people.
#FBCNews #FijiNews #Fiji

More:https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/flp-leader-calls-for-socio-economic-reforms/".
